    "Out-of-sample prediction accuracy was evaluated using a non-nested cross-validation with 10 outer folds and 5 repeats.",
    "A heuristic was used to efficiently calculate the hyperparameter C 106: c = 1",
    "where G is the matrix multiplication of features and transposition of features (here: functional connectivity).",
    "To investigate whether confounding effects impacted our results, standard confound variables (age and sex for the prediction of all phenotypes) were removed from the connectivity features using linear regression.",
    "Confound removal was performed within each training fold and the confound models were subsequently applied to test data to prevent data leakage 107."
